WEBVTT

00:33.867 --> 00:35.702
Ida's not your boo!

00:35.744 --> 00:36.703
Then why did I just
        spend the last two hours

00:36.745 --> 00:38.371
soaking in her tub?

00:38.413 --> 00:40.540
Congratulations.
        Chuck's a lucky guy.

00:40.582 --> 00:43.543
Can we maybe just table
     the wedding talk for a bit?

00:43.585 --> 00:44.878
I'm serious about my craft.

00:44.919 --> 00:46.129
I wish you were as serious

00:46.171 --> 00:47.547
about your social media
               presence.

00:47.589 --> 00:48.631
So what you saying?

00:48.673 --> 00:50.008
I gotta change my whole script?

00:50.050 --> 00:51.760
You finally got
        a good script, great.

00:51.801 --> 00:53.011
Now it's time
         to make it better.

00:53.053 --> 00:54.179
I'ma go ahead and head out.

00:54.220 --> 00:56.014
I got rid of
       one toxic relationship

00:56.056 --> 00:57.599
and walked right
          into another one.

00:57.640 --> 00:59.559
How the hell
         did you get fired?

00:59.601 --> 01:01.394
You still got the hook up
      at that delivery service?

01:08.777 --> 01:11.863
upbeat music playing

01:11.905 --> 01:13.281
What should
            our hashtag be?

01:13.323 --> 01:14.699
I don't know.

01:14.741 --> 01:15.909
It needs to
         be something good.

01:15.950 --> 01:17.744
People will remember
          the hashtag more

01:17.786 --> 01:18.578
than they'll remember
            the wedding.

01:18.620 --> 01:20.121
I would hope not.

01:20.163 --> 01:22.916
Honey, weddings this day
       and age can't be basic.

01:22.957 --> 01:24.459
Everybody's gonna have
          their phones out.

01:24.501 --> 01:26.336
People are gonna want a show,
     and we gotta give them one.

01:26.377 --> 01:28.588
This is our wedding,
   not opening night on Broadway.

01:28.630 --> 01:29.756
Of course not.

01:29.798 --> 01:30.924
This is way more
           nerve-wracking.

01:32.467 --> 01:35.261
Ugh, why does she always call
         at the worst times?

01:35.303 --> 01:37.931
-That's her superpower.
           -Hello, Mother.

01:39.474 --> 01:41.267
Are you trying to pawn
     somebody's engagement ring?

01:41.309 --> 01:43.520
No, darling,
        someone proposed to me.

01:43.561 --> 01:45.105
They did?

01:45.146 --> 01:46.231
Why is that so hard
              to believe?

01:46.272 --> 01:47.357
Because last weekend
         you were in Dallas

01:47.398 --> 01:48.691
at a singles convention.

01:48.733 --> 01:51.027
Well, it worked!

01:51.069 --> 01:52.570
Mom,
     please give that ring back

01:52.612 --> 01:53.905
to whatever weird man
           gave it to you,

01:53.947 --> 01:55.448
and then we can forget
         this ever happened.

01:55.490 --> 01:57.408
I will do no such thing.

01:57.450 --> 01:59.119
You aren't the only one
           who deserves love.

01:59.160 --> 02:00.912
Mother, if you bring
   a strange person to my wedding,

02:00.954 --> 02:02.080
I will never forgive you.

02:02.122 --> 02:04.749
Oh, you'll be fine. Ta-ta!

02:04.791 --> 02:06.584
Why is she like this?

02:06.626 --> 02:08.294
You and I both know
      that's a loaded question.

02:08.336 --> 02:09.671
Just because
          she was abandoned

02:09.712 --> 02:11.673
as a child doesn't give her
      the right to torture me.

02:11.714 --> 02:13.633
Actually, it does,
     and I think she's counting

02:13.675 --> 02:15.301
on you to break
       the generational curse.

02:15.343 --> 02:16.845
Must I do everything?

02:16.886 --> 02:20.473
Busy picking up
           the pieces, baby

02:20.515 --> 02:23.643
I haven't seen you
          around here, baby

02:23.685 --> 02:25.854
Oh, my God! I'm a GIF!

02:27.188 --> 02:29.315
People really love
           that show, huh?

02:29.357 --> 02:30.733
Don't step on my moment

02:30.775 --> 02:31.943
just 'cause you have
    to go back to the workforce.

02:31.985 --> 02:34.112
Ain't nobody stepping
           on your moment.

02:34.154 --> 02:36.156
I'm just saying, I don't think
            that's gonna

02:36.197 --> 02:37.991
catapult your ass to stardom,
             that's all.

02:38.032 --> 02:39.784
Well, I'm further
         than I was before.

02:39.826 --> 02:41.286
Are you?

02:41.327 --> 02:42.954
Being loved on social media
           is a big deal.

02:42.996 --> 02:45.331
If I can start building
          my own audience,

02:45.373 --> 02:47.667
pretty soon casting directors
         will be calling me.

02:47.709 --> 02:49.961
Yeah, but that gonna take
           a lot of work.

02:50.003 --> 02:51.462
Now you sound like Marie.

02:51.504 --> 02:53.006
That is shade
       that I do not receive.

02:53.047 --> 02:54.340
-It's true.
               -Mm-mm.

02:54.382 --> 02:55.758
You're a lot more
        practical these days.

02:55.800 --> 02:57.844
Am I?

02:57.886 --> 02:59.429
Maybe it's 'cause
        you been hanging out

02:59.470 --> 03:01.139
with a mogul lately.

03:01.181 --> 03:02.307
-Nah, that ain't it.
              -Mm-hmm.

03:02.348 --> 03:03.808
Mm-mm.

03:03.850 --> 03:05.643
I think she's
          rubbing off on you

03:05.685 --> 03:08.646
Shut up!
       Yo, forget what I said.

03:08.688 --> 03:11.566
You being a GIF is a big deal,
   and you should celebrate that.

03:11.608 --> 03:14.027
I will. But you're right.

03:14.068 --> 03:15.695
I can't let this kind of stuff
           get to my head

03:15.737 --> 03:17.030
'cause if I do,
   I'll just get too comfortable,

03:17.071 --> 03:18.573
and nothing good
         can come from that.

03:18.615 --> 03:20.158
Black women deserve comfort.

03:20.200 --> 03:22.535
When it comes to bedsheets,
       not when it comes to me

03:22.577 --> 03:24.495
trying to be
     America's Next Top Actress.

03:24.537 --> 03:26.206
-Mm.

03:26.247 --> 03:28.208
Oh, shit, that's me.
             I gotta go.

03:28.249 --> 03:30.126
Oh, but you didn't finish
       loading the dishwasher,

03:30.168 --> 03:31.669
and what you did load
            is all wrong.

03:31.711 --> 03:33.171
I'll fix it when I get back.

03:33.213 --> 03:35.673
Look, this delivery gig
       is not like Hollywood.

03:35.715 --> 03:37.342
If I'm late, I'm fired,
       and if I lose this job,

03:37.383 --> 03:38.635
I gotta move back in
            with my mom,

03:38.676 --> 03:41.846
and don't nobody want that,
           especially me.

03:41.888 --> 03:44.724
-I'll see you later.
               -Okay!

03:44.766 --> 03:45.975
Bye!
              Have fun.

03:48.061 --> 03:50.647
Oh, my God!

03:52.941 --> 03:54.525
upbeat music playing

03:54.567 --> 03:56.819
Get ready, get ready,
              get ready

03:56.861 --> 03:57.904
Get ready

04:04.869 --> 04:06.746
Oh, my bad. This the house?

04:06.788 --> 04:08.998
That's the house.

04:09.040 --> 04:10.333
What if somebody comes out

04:10.375 --> 04:11.751
and tells me
     to get off their property?

04:11.793 --> 04:14.629
Take the box, put it
     on the step, and come back.

04:14.671 --> 04:16.714
-That's it?
             -That's it.

04:17.840 --> 04:20.134
Damn, do you ever get bored
         of doing this shit?

04:20.176 --> 04:21.886
I actually enjoy it.

04:21.928 --> 04:23.429
-It's chill.
              -Mm-hmm.

04:23.471 --> 04:25.265
And I like everyone
            on my route.

04:25.306 --> 04:27.267
What if my route
           don't like me?

04:27.308 --> 04:28.726
Well, at this rate,
    you're not gonna have a route

04:28.768 --> 04:30.937
unless you get
    that package up by that door.

04:30.979 --> 04:33.773
You right. Be back.

04:39.612 --> 04:40.905
Well, hello there.

04:40.947 --> 04:42.824
Look at you.

04:42.865 --> 04:45.201
You like my uniform?
      I'm a working woman now.

04:45.243 --> 04:46.869
I see.

04:46.911 --> 04:48.579
Are you having
          a good first day?

04:48.621 --> 04:51.457
Hell no!
     It's hot as hell out here.

04:51.499 --> 04:54.460
And the guy that's training me
     won't let me play my music.

04:54.502 --> 04:56.546
And he keep acting like
     I'm getting on his nerves.

04:56.587 --> 04:57.547
That's because
          you probably are.

04:57.588 --> 04:59.882
No, I'm nervous.

04:59.924 --> 05:02.135
It's scary walking up
        to strangers' houses.

05:02.176 --> 05:03.761
People are crazy.

05:03.803 --> 05:05.263
Well, you're bringing them
      something that they want,

05:05.305 --> 05:07.473
so they'll probably welcome you
           with open arms.

05:07.515 --> 05:08.933
Anything I can bring to you?

05:08.975 --> 05:10.476
Just yourself.

05:10.518 --> 05:12.437
When you get off work.

05:12.478 --> 05:14.147
I mean, I can take a break
             right now.

05:14.188 --> 05:16.065
Nah, I don't want you
   losing your job because of me.

05:16.107 --> 05:17.400
You could always
            hire me back.

05:17.442 --> 05:19.485
I can't sleep
        with my subordinate.

05:19.527 --> 05:20.945
Then never mind.

05:20.987 --> 05:23.156
Can you deliver
        the package, please?

05:29.871 --> 05:31.497
Bye, you.

05:33.374 --> 05:35.335
"Bye, you?"

05:35.376 --> 05:38.379
Yeah, it feels weird
   calling her by her first name,

05:38.421 --> 05:40.590
but we don't really use
           pet names yet,

05:40.631 --> 05:43.217
so we basically don't know
      what to call each other.

05:43.259 --> 05:45.595
Sounds like a hot mess to me.

05:45.636 --> 05:48.473
You want to put
     your ear thingies back in?

05:58.566 --> 05:59.650
Yo

05:59.692 --> 06:01.194
Told you they had
          a big-ass house.

06:01.235 --> 06:03.446
Uh

06:03.488 --> 06:04.489
All right

06:04.530 --> 06:06.949
Uh, uh, uh, okay

06:06.991 --> 06:09.202
Cash in the air,
        cash in the air, yeah

06:09.243 --> 06:11.537
Cash in the air,
        cash in the air, yeah

06:11.579 --> 06:13.873
Let the money fall,
          let the money fall

06:13.915 --> 06:15.958
Let the money fall,
          let the money fall

06:18.669 --> 06:20.171
Welcome.

06:20.213 --> 06:22.298
I always knew
       Marie would marry rich.

06:24.008 --> 06:26.010
Yo, you think me and Ida
          will get married?

06:26.052 --> 06:27.845
I hope not.

06:27.887 --> 06:29.847
Why you always gotta shit
            on my dreams?

06:29.889 --> 06:30.932
This isn't about you.

06:30.973 --> 06:32.809
This is about
         our friend, Marie.

06:32.850 --> 06:34.936
You really excited
    about this bougie-ass union?

06:34.977 --> 06:36.437
Yes.

06:36.479 --> 06:39.565
Marie is about to have
      the wedding of my dreams.

06:39.607 --> 06:40.900
Oh, that's why
           you're excited.

06:40.942 --> 06:42.777
Because you get to live
      vicariously through her.

06:42.819 --> 06:44.529
I'm also happy
           for our friend.

06:44.570 --> 06:46.280
And you should be happy
            for her too.

06:46.322 --> 06:48.116
I am happy.
         Don't I look happy?

06:49.534 --> 06:50.952
You look nervous.

06:50.993 --> 06:53.830
Yeah, I always get nervous
          around rich folk.

06:53.871 --> 06:57.500
And they look--they got
           old money rich.

06:57.542 --> 07:01.712
Look at these curtains.
          Old-ass curtains.

07:01.754 --> 07:03.923
Probably silk.

07:14.475 --> 07:16.352
Hi.

07:51.012 --> 07:53.014
-What's so funny?
              -Nothing.

07:53.055 --> 07:54.974
Just a silly inside joke
        between me and Chuck.

07:55.016 --> 07:56.350
Well, the best jokes
            are the ones

07:56.392 --> 07:57.894
that everybody
        can laugh at, right?

07:57.935 --> 07:59.770
Very true.
         Excuse my rudeness.

07:59.812 --> 08:01.689
You're excused.

08:01.731 --> 08:04.108
These are my friends,
           Nia and Hattie.

08:04.150 --> 08:05.485
Ladies, this is Chance.

08:05.526 --> 08:07.862
He was forced to live
         with me in college.

08:07.904 --> 08:09.655
Has he always been
           this annoying?

08:09.697 --> 08:11.449
-Hattie!
                -Yes.

08:11.491 --> 08:12.575
Is he still making
         them damn smoothies

08:12.617 --> 08:13.618
first thing in the morning?

08:13.659 --> 08:15.286
Hell yes!

08:15.328 --> 08:17.497
If I don't have it,
     my whole day is thrown off.

08:17.538 --> 08:19.248
-Mm-hmm.
    -Are you sure we haven't met?

08:19.290 --> 08:21.000
You look so familiar.

08:21.042 --> 08:22.627
Are you a fan
         of   Cocoa's Butter   ?

08:22.668 --> 08:24.337
Maybe that's why
         you recognize her.

08:24.378 --> 08:27.089
No, but my mom and all
     my sisters love that show.

08:27.131 --> 08:28.466
I think somebody texted
              your face

08:28.508 --> 08:30.426
as a response
    to something I said earlier.

08:30.468 --> 08:32.512
Oh, my God!
      Someone sent you my GIF!

08:32.553 --> 08:33.679
-What?
            -Nia's a GIF?

08:33.721 --> 08:35.473
-I saw it this morning.
             -Big tings!

08:35.515 --> 08:37.225
Why didn't anybody tell me?

08:37.266 --> 08:38.601
Everything ain't
          about you, Marie.

08:38.643 --> 08:40.019
Do you mind
      if we take a quick photo?

08:40.061 --> 08:40.937
Are you gonna post it?

08:40.978 --> 08:42.188
Maybe.

08:44.774 --> 08:46.192
You're working that dress too.

08:46.234 --> 08:48.027
-Ooh, thank you.
         -Yeah, you welcome.

08:53.449 --> 08:55.409
-We look good together.
          -Ooh, yes.

08:55.451 --> 08:57.245
Our complexions
       complement each other.

08:57.286 --> 08:59.330
We'd have some
       beautiful brown babies.

08:59.372 --> 09:02.208
Oh, boy, girl,
    then another boy is my dream.

09:02.250 --> 09:04.168
I like the idea.
        Two boys and a girl,

09:04.210 --> 09:05.711
so she can be the princess.

09:05.753 --> 09:06.712
How about y'all
           let y'all kids

09:06.754 --> 09:08.631
tell you how they identify?

09:08.673 --> 09:11.467
Damn, that's why
        we so messed up now.

09:11.509 --> 09:13.886
Chance, I got some folks
         I want you to meet.

09:16.597 --> 09:18.724
Is it just me,
    or is that my future husband?

09:18.766 --> 09:20.017
Oh, it's just you.

09:20.059 --> 09:20.893
Girl, that ain't
            your husband.

09:26.732 --> 09:29.735
They're gonna have
      such a beautiful wedding.

09:29.777 --> 09:31.404
Hey, babe,
   do you want to go take a photo

09:31.445 --> 09:33.072
in front of the lake
        with all those swans?

09:33.114 --> 09:35.616
Oh, I mean,
      I can take your picture.

09:35.658 --> 09:37.368
Do you not want to be
            seen with me?

09:37.410 --> 09:39.829
What?
    Of course, I do. I love you.

09:39.870 --> 09:42.873
Well, you've just been acting
      really weird on socials.

09:42.915 --> 09:44.292
Nah, I barely even go
          on social media.

09:44.333 --> 09:46.919
You've archived a lot
       of our photos together.

09:46.961 --> 09:48.921
'Cause I have a big job now.

09:48.963 --> 09:50.840
I don't want people all up
           in my business.

09:50.881 --> 09:52.717
It shouldn't be about
           who I'm dating.

09:52.758 --> 09:54.176
It should be about the work
          I'm putting out.

09:54.218 --> 09:55.469
Okay.

09:55.511 --> 09:56.971
Come on, I'm not that guy.

09:57.013 --> 09:58.639
-Huh?
               -Fine.

10:00.266 --> 10:01.976
You know, weddings
        always make me think

10:02.018 --> 10:03.102
about
        what it would be like

10:03.144 --> 10:04.395
if I were the one
          getting married.

10:04.437 --> 10:06.105
Uh-huh.

10:06.147 --> 10:07.481
Have you ever thought about
        what it would be like

10:07.523 --> 10:08.524
if we were to get married?

10:08.566 --> 10:10.192
What?

10:10.234 --> 10:12.361
Have you thought about us
       getting married at all?

10:12.403 --> 10:15.281
Oh, babe, I have so much
     to do before I get married.

10:15.323 --> 10:18.367
But as soon as I get my shit
    together, you know I got you.

10:18.409 --> 10:20.953
-Love you.
