      to step up my engagement.

10:51.859 --> 10:53.611
Social engagement, I mean.

10:53.653 --> 10:54.820
I know what you mean.

10:56.989 --> 10:58.449
Folks on the Internet
             aren't just

10:58.491 --> 11:00.493
a bunch of bots and trolls.

11:00.534 --> 11:02.286
They're real people
         with real feelings

11:02.328 --> 11:03.954
that just want to be heard.

11:03.996 --> 11:06.207
-And I'm all ears.
              -Me too.

11:08.042 --> 11:10.544
The VP before me thought
    that social media was a fad,

11:10.586 --> 11:12.797
that it would just go away.

11:12.838 --> 11:15.341
Guess what?
    It impacts everything we do.

11:15.383 --> 11:17.843
If people are talking,
          I want to listen.

11:17.885 --> 11:19.845
They're the ones
      we're selling to anyway.

11:19.887 --> 11:21.847
We might as well join forces.

11:21.889 --> 11:23.349
I never thought
         about it that way.

11:23.391 --> 11:24.850
We have a direct connect
          to our customer,

11:24.892 --> 11:26.852
and if we worked together,
      everyone could be happy.

11:26.894 --> 11:28.688
I don't know, that sounds
    a little too good to be true.

11:28.729 --> 11:30.356
You're right.

11:30.398 --> 11:31.857
This could totally
         blow up in my face.

11:31.899 --> 11:34.694
-It really could.
      -But what if it doesn't?

11:36.654 --> 11:38.155
Ba-da-ba-dum

11:38.197 --> 11:41.367
Bum, bum, ba-dum,
             bum-bum-bum

11:41.409 --> 11:43.786
She's got that cornbread
